      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Papers, chiefly 1858-1889, of the Calfee family of
         southwest Virginia. Includes letters written from Texas by
         Calvin J. Calfee and letters written by Confederate soldiers
         David H. Calfee, James Calfee, L. S. Calfee and William B.
         Calfee as well as deeds for land in Pulaski and Wythe
         counties, Virginia.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement>
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <arrangement>
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>This collection is arranged into series, then
            alphebetically by person's name, and finally
            chronologically by date.</p>
         </arrangement>
         <arrangement>
            <head>Organization</head>
            <p>This collection has been organized into 4 series: 
            <lb />1. Correspondence 
            <lb />2. Vouchers 
            <lb />3. Legal Papers 
            <lb />4. Other Papers.</p>
         </arrangement>
      </arrangement>
